{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906468838,"sessionID":"ses_283ba050affedrzETAwxPuy0Ec","part":{"id":"prt_d7c462c4e001NDaAjvatbHwO5E","messageID":"msg_d7c461618001z149PEs4bPhjwf","sessionID":"ses_283ba050affedrzETAwxPuy0Ec","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-08ca0afd826641f2826ade1210b8eacb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775906468813,"end":1775906468836}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906468841,"sessionID":"ses_283ba050affedrzETAwxPuy0Ec","part":{"id":"prt_d7c463027001WfQ0ZJG2Q44I4h","messageID":"msg_d7c461618001z149PEs4bPhjwf","sessionID":"ses_283ba050affedrzETAwxPuy0Ec","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0487a2349dac414eae02f21c2b4bdbbb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n6: \n7: | Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n8: |--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n9: | `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n10: | `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n11: | `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n12: | `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Directory Structure\n19: \n20: ```\n21: cmd/\n22: ├── picod/\n23: │   ├── main.go              # PicoD entry point (implemented)\n24: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n25: ├── router/\n26: │   ├── main.go              # Router entry point\n27: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n28: ├── workloadmanager/\n29: │   ├── main.go              # WorkloadManager entry point\n30: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n31: └── agentd/\n32: │   ├── main.go              # Agentd entry point\n33: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Binary Dependency Graph\n37: \n38: ```\n39: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                            CLI Binaries                                       │\n41: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n42: │                                                                               │\n43: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n44: │   │   picod   │     │   router  │     │workloadmanager│     │  agentd   │   │\n45: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n46: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n47: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n48: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n49: │   │ pkg/picod │     │pkg/router │     │pkg/workload   │     │pkg/agentd │   │\n50: │   │           │     │           │     │   manager     │     │           │   │\n51: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n52: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n53: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n54: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n55: │   │                    Common Dependencies                                 │ │\n56: │   │  - k8s.io/klog/v2 (logging)                                           │ │\n57: │   │  - github.com/spf13/pflag (flags)                                     │ │\n58: │   │  - context, os, signal                                                │ │\n59: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: │                                                                               │\n61: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Deployment Model\n65: \n66: ```\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n69: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n70: │                                                                  │\n71: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n72: │  │ router Deployment│    │workloadmanager   │                  │\n73: │  │    (Pod :8080)   │───▶│ Deployment       │                  │\n74: │  └──────────────────┘    │   (Pod :8080)    │                  │\n75: │           │              └──────────────────┘                  │\n76: │           │                      │                              │\n77: │           ▼                      ▼                              │\n78: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n79: │  │ Redis/Valkey     │    │  K8s API Server  │                  │\n80: │  │ (Session Store)  │    │  (CRDs, Pods)    │                  │\n81: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘                  │\n82: │                                                                  │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n84: │  │ agentd Deployment│    (Leader Election enabled)             │\n85: │  │  (Controller)    │                                           │\n86: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n87: │                                                                  │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: \n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                      Sandbox Pod                                 │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n94: │  │ picod sidecar    │    (Local code execution)                │\n95: │  │   (Port 8080)    │                                           │\n96: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### Common CLI Configuration Pattern\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: package main\n108: \n109: type CLIConfig struct {\n110:     LogLevel    string `flag:\"log-level\" default:\"info\" usage:\"Log level (debug, info, warn, error)\"`\n111:     MetricsAddr string `flag:\"metrics-addr\" default:\"0\" usage:\"Metrics server address (0 to disable)\"`\n112:     HealthAddr  string `flag:\"health-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Health check server address\"`\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### PicoD CLI Configuration\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: package main\n120: \n121: type PicoDConfig struct {\n122:     CLIConfig\n123:     Port         int    `flag:\"port\" default:\"8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n124:     Workspace    string `flag:\"workspace\" default:\"\" usage:\"Workspace directory path\"`\n125:     AuthEnabled  bool   `flag:\"auth-enabled\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable authentication\"`\n126:     MaxExecTime  int    `flag:\"max-exec-time\" default:\"30\" usage:\"Maximum execution time in seconds\"`\n127:     MaxFileSize  int64  `flag:\"max-file-size\" default:\"10485760\" usage:\"Maximum file size in bytes\"`\n128:     SanitizeRoot string `flag:\"sanitize-root\" default:\"\" usage:\"Root directory for path sanitization\"`\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Router CLI Configuration\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: package main\n136: \n137: type RouterConfig struct {\n138:     CLIConfig\n139:     Port                 string `flag:\"port\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n140:     MaxConcurrentRequests int   `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"1000\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent requests\"`\n141:     Debug                bool   `flag:\"debug\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable debug mode\"`\n142:     EnableTLS            bool   `flag:\"enable-tls\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable TLS\"`\n143:     TLSCert              string `flag:\"tls-cert\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS certificate file\"`\n144:     TLSKey               string `flag:\"tls-key\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS key file\"`\n145:     StoreAddr            string `flag:\"store-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey address\"`\n146:     StorePassword        string `flag:\"store-password\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey password\"`\n147:     StoreType            string `flag:\"store-type\" default:\"redis\" usage:\"Store type (redis, valkey)\"`\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### WorkloadManager CLI Configuration\n152: \n153: ```go\n154: package main\n155: \n156: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n157:     CLIConfig\n158:     Addr              string        `flag:\"addr\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP server address\"`\n159:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"read-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP read timeout\"`\n160:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration `flag:\"write-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP write timeout\"`\n161:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"idle-timeout\" default:\"90s\" usage:\"HTTP idle timeout\"`\n162:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration `flag:\"shutdown-timeout\" default:\"10s\" usage:\"Graceful shutdown timeout\"`\n163:     GCInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"gc-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Garbage collection interval\"`\n164:     GCOnceTimeout     time.Duration `flag:\"gc-once-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"Single GC run timeout\"`\n165:     Kubeconfig        string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n166:     MasterURL         string        `flag:\"master-url\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes API server URL\"`\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Agentd CLI Configuration\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: package main\n174: \n175: type AgentdConfig struct {\n176:     CLIConfig\n177:     IdleThreshold        time.Duration `flag:\"idle-threshold\" default:\"30m\" usage:\"Idle threshold for cleanup\"`\n178:     CheckInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"check-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Cleanup check interval\"`\n179:     MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"10\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent cleanups\"`\n180:     Namespaces           []string      `flag:\"namespace\" default:\"default\" usage:\"Namespaces to watch\"`\n181:     LeaderElection       bool          `flag:\"leader-election\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable leader election\"`\n182:     LeaderElectionID     string        `flag:\"leader-election-id\" default:\"agentcube-agentd\" usage:\"Leader election ID\"`\n183:     Kubeconfig           string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## API Contracts\n190: \n191: ### Binary Entry Point Interface\n192: \n193: Each binary follows this pattern:\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: package main\n197: \n198: type Binary interface {\n199:     InitFlags() *Config\n200:     ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error\n201:     Run(ctx context.Context, cfg *Config) error\n202:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n203: }\n204: \n205: func main() {\n206:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n207:     flag.Parse()\n208:     \n209:     cfg := InitFlags()\n210:     if err := ValidateConfig(cfg); err != nil {\n211:         klog.Fatalf(\"invalid config: %v\", err)\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214:     \n215:     ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n216:     defer cancel()\n217:     \n218:     if err := Run(ctx, cfg); err != nil {\n219:         klog.Fatalf(\"run error: %v\", err)\n220:         os.Exit(1)\n221:     }\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ### Signal Handling Contract\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: package main\n229: \n230: func setupSignalHandler() context.Context {\n231:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n232:     \n233:     c := make(chan os.Signal, 2)\n234:     signal.Notify(c, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n235:     \n236:     go func() {\n237:         sig := <-c\n238:         klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n239:         cancel()\n240:         \n241:         if sig == syscall.SIGKILL {\n242:             <-c\n243:             klog.InfoS(\"received second signal, forcing exit\")\n244:             os.Exit(1)\n245:         }\n246:     }()\n247:     \n248:     return ctx\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Health Check Contract\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: package main\n256: \n257: type HealthChecker interface {\n258:     Live() bool\n259:     Ready() bool\n260: }\n261: \n262: func (h *HealthServer) Start(addr string) error {\n263:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n264:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/live\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n265:         if h.Live() {\n266:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n267:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n268:         } else {\n269:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n270:         }\n271:     })\n272:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/ready\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n273:         if h.Ready() {\n274:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n275:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n276:         } else {\n277:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n278:         }\n279:     })\n280:     return http.ListenAndServe(addr, mux)\n281: }\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### Flag Registration Contract\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: package main\n288: \n289: func InitFlags() *Config {\n290:     cfg := &Config{}\n291:     \n292:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n293:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n294:     \n295:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LogLevel, \"log-level\", \"info\", \"Log level\")\n296:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.MetricsAddr, \"metrics-addr\", \"0\", \"Metrics address\")\n297:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.HealthAddr, \"health-addr\", \"\", \"Health address\")\n298:     \n299:     flag.Parse()\n300:     \n301:     return cfg\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Binary Implementation Details\n308: \n309: ### 1. picod (cmd/picod/main.go)\n310: \n311: **Purpose**: Local code execution daemon running as a sidecar in sandbox pods.\n312: \n313: **Current Implementation** (pkg/picod/server.go:26-77):\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: func main() {\n317:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n318:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n319: \n320:     port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"HTTP listening port\")\n321:     workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Workspace directory path\")\n322:     flag.Parse()\n323: \n324:     config := &picod.Config{\n325:         Port:      *port,\n326:         Workspace: *workspace,\n327:     }\n328: \n329:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n330:     if err != nil {\n331:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)\n332:         os.Exit(1)\n333:     }\n334: \n335:     if err := server.Run(context.Background()); err != nil {\n336:         klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n337:         os.Exit(1)\n338:     }\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Endpoints**:\n343: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n344: |------|--------|---------|\n345: | `/health` | GET | Health check |\n346: | `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code |\n347: | `/api/files` | POST | Upload file |\n348: | `/api/files` | GET | List files |\n349: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file |\n350: \n351: ### 2. router (cmd/router/main.go)\n352: \n353: **Purpose**: Session routing and reverse proxy for agent/code interpreter invocations.\n354: \n355: **Implementation Template**:\n356: \n357: ```go\n358: func main() {\n359:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n360:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n361:     \n362:     cfg := &RouterConfig{}\n363:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Port, \"port\", \":8080\", \"HTTP listening port\")\n364:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreAddr, \"store-addr\", \"\", \"Redis/Valkey address\")\n365:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreType, \"store-type\", \"redis\", \"Store type\")\n366:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests, \"max-concurrent\", 1000, \"Max concurrent requests\")\n367:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.Debug, \"debug\", false, \"Enable debug mode\")\n368:     flag.Parse()\n369:     \n370:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n371:     \n372:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n373:     if err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376:     \n377:     sessionManager := router.NewSessionManager(store)\n378:     jwtManager := router.NewJWTManager()\n379:     \n380:     server := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n381:         Port:                 cfg.Port,\n382:         MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n383:         Debug:                cfg.Debug,\n384:     }, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, klog.Logger{})\n385:     \n386:     if err := server.Start(ctx); err != nil {\n387:         klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)\n388:     }\n389: }\n390: ```\n391: \n392: **Endpoints**:\n393: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n394: |------|--------|---------|\n395: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n396: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n397: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy |\n398: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy |\n399: \n400: ### 3. workloadmanager (cmd/workloadmanager/main.go)\n401: \n402: **Purpose**: Workload manager HTTP server for sandbox lifecycle management.\n403: \n404: **Implementation Template**:\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: func main() {\n408:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n409:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n410:     \n411:     cfg := &WorkloadManagerConfig{}\n412:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Addr, \"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n413:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.ReadTimeout, \"read-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Read timeout\")\n414:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.WriteTimeout, \"write-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Write timeout\")\n415:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.GCInterval, \"gc-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"GC interval\")\n416:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Kubeconfig path\")\n417:     flag.Parse()\n418:     \n419:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n420:     \n421:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(cfg.Kubeconfig, cfg.MasterURL)\n422:     if err != nil {\n423:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n424:     }\n425:     \n426:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n427:     if err != nil {\n428:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(\n432:         workloadmanager.Config{\n433:             Addr:            cfg.Addr,\n434:             ReadTimeout:     cfg.ReadTimeout,\n435:             WriteTimeout:    cfg.WriteTimeout,\n436:             ShutdownTimeout: cfg.ShutdownTimeout,\n437:         },\n438:         klog.Logger{},\n439:         k8sClient,\n440:         store,\n441:     )\n442:     \n443:     server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n444:     server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(k8sClient, store))\n445:     \n446:     server.GracefulShutdown()\n447:     \n448:     errCh := server.Start()\n449:     select {\n450:     case err := <-errCh:\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"workloadmanager error: %v\", err)\n452:     case <-ctx.Done():\n453:         server.Stop(context.Background())\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: **Endpoints**:\n459: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n460: |------|--------|---------|\n461: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n462: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n463: | `/sandboxes` | POST | Create sandbox |\n464: | `/sandboxes/:id` | GET | Get sandbox |\n465: | `/sandboxes/:id` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n466: \n467: ### 4. agentd (cmd/agentd/main.go)\n468: \n469: **Purpose**: Kubernetes controller for idle resource cleanup using controller-runtime.\n470: \n471: **Implementation Template**:\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func main() {\n475:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n476:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n477:     \n478:     cfg := &AgentdConfig{}\n479:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.IdleThreshold, \"idle-threshold\", 30*time.Minute, \"Idle threshold\")\n480:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.CheckInterval, \"check-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"Check interval\")\n481:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup, \"max-concurrent\", 10, \"Max concurrent cleanups\")\n482:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.LeaderElection, \"leader-election\", true, \"Enable leader election\")\n483:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LeaderElectionID, \"leader-election-id\", \"agentcube-agentd\", \"Leader election ID\")\n484:     flag.Parse()\n485:     \n486:     k8sConfig, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n487:     if err != nil {\n488:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to get k8s config: %v\", err)\n489:     }\n490:     \n491:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(k8sConfig, ctrl.Options{\n492:         LeaderElection:          cfg.LeaderElection,\n493:         LeaderElectionID:        cfg.LeaderElectionID,\n494:         LeaderElectionNamespace: \"default\",\n495:     })\n496:     if err != nil {\n497:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create manager: %v\", err)\n498:     }\n499:     \n500:     if err := agentd.SetupIdleCleanupController(mgr, cfg); err != nil {\n501:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup controller: %v\", err)\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     klog.InfoS(\"starting agentd controller\")\n505:     if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n506:         klog.Fatalf(\"controller error: %v\", err)\n507:     }\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ---\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Categories\n516: \n517: | Category | Description | Action |\n518: |----------|-------------|--------|\n519: | `ErrConfigInvalid` | Configuration validation failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n520: | `ErrStoreConnect` | Store connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n521: | `ErrK8sConnect` | Kubernetes connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n522: | `ErrServerStart` | HTTP server start failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n523: | `ErrSignalReceived` | Graceful shutdown triggered | Log info, cancel context |\n524: | `ErrShutdownTimeout` | Shutdown exceeded timeout | Log warning, force exit |\n525: \n526: ### Error Handling Pattern\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: func handleStartupError(component string, err error) {\n530:     if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n531:         klog.InfoS(\"shutdown requested\")\n532:         return\n533:     }\n534:     \n535:     if errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGTERM) || errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGINT) {\n536:         klog.InfoS(\"received termination signal\", \"signal\", err)\n537:         return\n538:     }\n539:     \n540:     klog.ErrorS(err, \"startup failure\", \"component\", component)\n541:     os.Exit(1)\n542: }\n543: ```\n544: \n545: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n546: \n547: ```\n548: 1. Signal received (SIGTERM/SIGINT)\n549: 2. Cancel main context\n550: 3. Stop accepting new requests\n551: 4. Wait for in-flight requests (timeout configurable)\n552: 5. Close store connections\n553: 6. Close K8s client connections\n554: 7. Exit with code 0\n555: ```\n556: \n557: ### Validation Errors\n558: \n559: ```go\n560: func ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error {\n561:     if cfg.Port <= 0 || cfg.Port > 65535 {\n562:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid port: %d\", cfg.Port)\n563:     }\n564:     \n565:     if cfg.IdleThreshold < 0 {\n566:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid idle threshold: %v\", cfg.IdleThreshold)\n567:     }\n568:     \n569:     if cfg.CheckInterval < 0 {\n570:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid check interval: %v\", cfg.CheckInterval)\n571:     }\n572:     \n573:     if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup < 0 {\n574:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid max concurrent cleanup: %d\", cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup)\n575:     }\n576:     \n577:     return nil\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Testing Strategy\n584: \n585: ### Unit Tests\n586: \n587: #### Flag Parsing Tests\n588: \n589: ```go\n590: func TestInitFlags(t *testing.T) {\n591:     tests := []struct {\n592:         name     string\n593:         args     []string\n594:         expected *Config\n595:     }{\n596:         {\n597:             name: \"default values\",\n598:             args: []string{},\n599:             expected: &Config{\n600:                 Port:           8080,\n601:                 LogLevel:       \"info\",\n602:                 IdleThreshold:  30 * time.Minute,\n603:             },\n604:         },\n605:         {\n606:             name: \"custom port\",\n607:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\"},\n608:             expected: &Config{\n609:                 Port:          9000,\n610:             },\n611:         },\n612:         {\n613:             name: \"multiple flags\",\n614:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\", \"-debug\", \"true\"},\n615:             expected: &Config{\n616:                 Port:  9000,\n617:                 Debug: true,\n618:             },\n619:         },\n620:     }\n621:     \n622:     for _, tt := range tests {\n623:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n624:             fs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"test\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n625:             cfg := &Config{}\n626:             setupFlags(fs, cfg)\n627:             \n628:             err := fs.Parse(tt.args)\n629:             require.NoError(t, err)\n630:             \n631:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expected.Port, cfg.Port)\n632:         })\n633:     }\n634: }\n635: ```\n636: \n637: #### Signal Handler Tests\n638: \n639: ```go\n640: func TestSignalHandler(t *testing.T) {\n641:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n642:     \n643:     syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n644:     \n645:     select {\n646:     case <-ctx.Done():\n647:         assert.True(t, true)\n648:     case <-time.After(5 * time.Second):\n649:         t.Fatal(\"signal handler did not cancel context\")\n650:     }\n651: }\n652: ```\n653: \n654: #### Config Validation Tests\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func TestValidateConfig(t *testing.T) {\n658:     tests := []struct {\n659:         name        string\n660:         config      *Config\n661:         expectError bool\n662:     }{\n663:         {\n664:             name: \"valid config\",\n665:             config: &Config{\n666:                 Port:          8080,\n667:                 IdleThreshold: 30 * time.Minute,\n668:             },\n669:             expectError: false,\n670:         },\n671:         {\n672:             name: \"invalid port\",\n673:             config: &Config{\n674:                 Port: -1,\n675:             },\n676:             expectError: true,\n677:         },\n678:         {\n679:             name: \"invalid idle threshold\",\n680:             config: &Config{\n681:                 IdleThreshold: -1 * time.Minute,\n682:             },\n683:             expectError: true,\n684:         },\n685:     }\n686:     \n687:     for _, tt := range tests {\n688:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n689:             err := ValidateConfig(tt.config)\n690:             if tt.expectError {\n691:                 assert.Error(t, err)\n692:             } else {\n693:                 assert.NoError(t, err)\n694:             }\n695:         })\n696:     }\n697: }\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ### Integration Tests\n701: \n702: #### Binary Startup Tests\n703: \n704: ```go\n705: func TestBinaryStartup(t *testing.T) {\n706:     if testing.Short() {\n707:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n708:     }\n709:     \n710:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"picod\")\n711:     \n712:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \"18080\")\n713:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n714:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n715:     \n716:     err := cmd.Start()\n717:     require.NoError(t, err)\n718:     \n719:     defer cmd.Process.Kill()\n720:     \n721:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n722:         resp, err := http.Get(\"http://localhost:18080/health\")\n723:         if err != nil {\n724:             return false\n725:         }\n726:         defer resp.Body.Close()\n727:         return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n728:     }, 10*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n729: }\n730: ```\n731: \n732: #### Graceful Shutdown Tests\n733: \n734: ```go\n735: func TestGracefulShutdown(t *testing.T) {\n736:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"router\")\n737:     \n738:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \":18080\", \"-store-type\", \"memory\")\n739:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n740:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n741:     \n742:     err := cmd.Start()\n743:     require.NoError(t, err)\n744:     \n745:     waitForHealthy(t, \"http://localhost:18080/health/live\")\n746:     \n747:     syscall.Kill(cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGTERM)\n748:     \n749:     done := make(chan error, 1)\n750:     go func() {\n751:         done <- cmd.Wait()\n752:     }()\n753:     \n754:     select {\n755:     case err := <-done:\n756:         assert.NoError(t, err)\n757:     case <-time.After(15 * time.Second):\n758:         t.Fatal(\"binary did not shutdown within timeout\")\n759:     }\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: ### Build Tests\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: func TestBuildAllBinaries(t *testing.T) {\n767:     binaries := []string{\"picod\", \"router\", \"workloadmanager\", \"agentd\"}\n768:     \n769:     for _, binary := range binaries {\n770:         t.Run(binary, func(t *testing.T) {\n771:             cmd := exec.Command(\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", \"/tmp/\"+binary, \"./cmd/\"+binary)\n772:             output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n773:             assert.NoError(t, err, \"build output: %s\", output)\n774:             \n775:             assert.FileExists(t, \"/tmp/\"+binary)\n776:         })\n777:     }\n778: }\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ---\n782: \n783: ## Metrics\n784: \n785: ### Prometheus Metrics\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: var (\n789:     startupDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n790:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_startup_duration_seconds\",\n792:             Help: \"Time taken for binary startup\",\n793:         },\n794:         []string{\"binary\"},\n795:     )\n796:     \n797:     shutdownDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n798:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n799:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_shutdown_duration_seconds\",\n800:             Help: \"Time taken for graceful shutdown\",\n801:         },\n802:         []string{\"binary\"},\n803:     )\n804:     \n805:     configReloadCount = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n806:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n807:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_config_reload_total\",\n808:             Help: \"Number of configuration reloads\",\n809:         },\n810:         []string{\"binary\"},\n811:     )\n812: )\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ---\n816: \n817: ## Configuration\n818: \n819: ### Environment Variables\n820: \n821: | Variable | Binary | Purpose |\n822: |----------|--------|---------|\n823: | `PORT` | picod, router, workloadmanager | HTTP port override |\n824: | `WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n825: | `STORE_ADDR` | router, workloadmanager | Redis/Valkey address |\n826: | `STORE_TYPE` | router, workloadmanager | Store backend type |\n827: | `KUBECONFIG` | workloadmanager, agentd | Kubernetes config path |\n828: | `LOG_LEVEL` | all | Log level override |\n829: \n830: ### Command-Line Flags Summary\n831: \n832: | Flag | Default | Purpose |\n833: |------|---------|---------|\n834: | `-port` | 8080 | HTTP listening port |\n835: | `-workspace` | current dir | Workspace directory (picod) |\n836: | `-idle-threshold` | 30m | Idle cleanup threshold (agentd) |\n837: | `-check-interval` | 5m | Cleanup check interval (agentd) |\n838: | `-leader-election` | true | Enable leader election (agentd) |\n839: | `-kubeconfig` | in-cluster | Kubernetes config path |\n840: | `-debug` | false | Enable debug mode (router) |\n841: | `-metrics-addr` | 0 | Prometheus metrics address |\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Build Configuration\n846: \n847: ### Go Module\n848: \n849: ```go\n850: // go.mod\n851: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n852: \n853: go 1.24\n854: \n855: require (\n856:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.x\n857:     github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.x\n858:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.x\n859:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.x\n860: )\n861: ```\n862: \n863: ### Makefile Targets\n864: \n865: ```makefile\n866: .PHONY: build clean\n867: \n868: build:\n869: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n870: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n871: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n872: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n873: \n874: clean:\n875: \trm -rf bin/\n876: \n877: build-picod:\n878: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n879: \n880: build-router:\n881: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n882: \n883: build-workloadmanager:\n884: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n885: \n886: build-agentd:\n887: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ### Docker Build\n891: \n892: ```dockerfile\n893: # Dockerfile for picod\n894: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n895: WORKDIR /app\n896: COPY . .\n897: RUN go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n898: \n899: FROM alpine:3.19\n900: COPY --from=builder /picod /picod\n901: ENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n902: ```\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## Implementation Checklist\n907: \n908: - [x] `cmd/picod/main.go` - PicoD entry point (implemented)\n909: - [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` - Router entry point\n910: - [ ] `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` - WorkloadManager entry point\n911: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` - Agentd entry point\n912: - [ ] Common signal handling package\n913: - [ ] Common flag validation utilities\n914: - [ ] Health check server integration\n915: - [ ] Metrics server integration\n916: - [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing\n917: - [ ] Unit tests for config validation\n918: - [ ] Integration tests for binary startup\n919: - [ ] Integration tests for graceful shutdown\n920: - [ ] Makefile build targets\n921: - [ ] Docker build configurations\n922: - [ ] Helm deployment manifests\n923: \n924: ---\n925: \n926: ## Dependencies\n927: \n928: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n929: |---------|---------|---------|\n930: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n931: | `github.com/spf13/pflag` | v1.x | POSIX/GNU-style flags |\n932: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities (agentd) |\n933: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.x | HTTP framework (picod, router) |\n934: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | v5.x | HTTP framework (workloadmanager) |\n935: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |\n\n(End of file - total 935 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n|--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n| `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n| `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n| `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n| `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775906468816,"end":1775906468838}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906468848,"sessionID":"ses_283ba050affedrzETAwxPuy0Ec","part":{"id":"prt_d7c46336c001rFrJRdCJchKogp","messageID":"msg_d7c461618001z149PEs4bPhjwf","sessionID":"ses_283ba050affedrzETAwxPuy0Ec","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f8dd7a9c0f294a659a643620191f53f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: Architecture Design Documentation & API Documentation\n2: \n3: **AR:** AR-043 — 架构设计文档与 API 文档  \n4: **Module:** docs  \n5: **Language:** Markdown  \n6: **Size:** M\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## OpenSpec Format\n11: \n12: Each requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## REQ-001: System Architecture Overview Documentation\n17: \n18: ### Description\n19: \n20: Provide comprehensive system architecture documentation explaining AgentCube's core components, deployment topology, and interaction flows.\n21: \n22: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Architecture overview page exists\n25: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus documentation site at `docs/docs/architecture/`\n26: - **WHEN** a user navigates to the architecture overview page\n27: - **THEN** a file `overview.md` exists in the architecture directory\n28: - **AND** the page renders successfully in Docusaurus\n29: - **AND** the content includes high-level system purpose and tech stack\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Architecture includes component diagram\n32: - **GIVEN** the architecture overview documentation\n33: - **WHEN** the document is viewed\n34: - **THEN** an ASCII or Mermaid diagram shows the system topology:\n35:   - Router ↔ Redis/Valkey ↔ WorkloadManager ↔ K8s API\n36:   - Sandbox Pods with PicoD daemon\n37:   - Agentd idle cleanup controller\n38: - **AND** the diagram uses clear component labels and arrows showing data flow\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Tech stack table is documented\n41: - **GIVEN** the architecture overview page\n42: - **WHEN** the tech stack section is viewed\n43: - **THEN** a table lists each technology layer:\n44:   - Go 1.24 for server components\n45:   - Python ≥3.10 for CLI/SDK\n46:   - Gin (Go HTTP framework)\n47:   - Kubernetes CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`)\n48:   - Redis/Valkey for session storage\n49:   - JWT RS256 for authentication\n50: - **AND** each technology has a purpose column explaining its role\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Deployment topology is explained\n53: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n54: - **WHEN** the deployment topology section is viewed\n55: - **THEN** the document describes three deployment patterns:\n56:   1. Router as Deployment (Pod :8080)\n57:   2. WorkloadManager as Deployment with Redis connection\n58:   3. Sandbox Pods with optional PicoD sidecar\n59: - **AND** each deployment pattern has resource requirements and scaling notes\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## REQ-002: Component Architecture Documentation\n64: \n65: ### Description\n66: \n67: Document each major system component with detailed architecture, responsibilities, and integration points.\n68: \n69: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Router component architecture page exists\n72: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation directory\n73: - **WHEN** a user views the Router component page (`router.md`)\n74: - **THEN** the document explains Router's role:\n75:   - Session routing and reverse proxy\n76:   - JWT token validation\n77:   - Traffic routing to sandbox pods\n78: - **AND** the page includes:\n79:   - Request flow diagram\n80:   - Session management logic description\n81:   - Supported endpoints table (`/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path`)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager component documentation\n84: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n85: - **WHEN** a user views the WorkloadManager component page (`workloadmanager.md`)\n86: - **THEN** the document describes:\n87:   - Sandbox lifecycle management (create, delete, garbage collection)\n88:   - Kubernetes API interactions (CRDs, Pods, Secrets)\n89:   - Health check and metrics endpoints\n90: - **AND** includes endpoint documentation:\n91:   - `/sandboxes` POST (create sandbox)\n92:   - `/sandboxes/:id` GET/DELETE\n93:   - `/health/live` and `/health/ready`\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: PicoD daemon architecture documented\n96: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation directory\n97: - **WHEN** a user views the PicoD component page (`picod.md`)\n98: - **THEN** the document explains:\n99:   - Local code execution daemon running as sidecar\n100:   - Workspace isolation and sanitization\n101:   - File operations (upload, download, list)\n102:   - Code execution timeout management\n103: - **AND** provides endpoint details:\n104:   - `/api/execute` POST for code execution\n105:   - `/api/files` POST/GET for file operations\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Agentd idle cleanup controller documented\n108: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n109: - **WHEN** the Agentd component page (`agentd.md`) is viewed\n110: - **THEN** the document explains:\n111:   - Kubernetes controller-runtime architecture\n112:   - Idle threshold detection logic\n113:   - Leader election for singleton controller\n114:   - Cleanup workflow steps\n115: - **AND** includes configuration parameters documentation:\n116:   - `--idle-threshold` (default 30m)\n117:   - `--check-interval` (default 5m)\n118:   - `--leader-election` flag\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## REQ-003: Data Flow Documentation\n123: \n124: ### Description\n125: \n126: Document how data flows through the system for key operations (sandbox creation, code execution, session routing).\n127: \n128: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Sandbox creation flow documented\n131: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n132: - **WHEN** the data flow section is viewed\n133: - **THEN** a step-by-step flow diagram exists for sandbox creation:\n134:   1. SDK → Router (JWT authenticated request)\n135:   2. Router → WorkloadManager (sandbox creation request)\n136:   3. WorkloadManager → Kubernetes API (create Pod, Secret, CRDs)\n137:   4. WorkloadManager → Router (return sandbox endpoint)\n138:   5. Router → SDK (session response with sandbox URL)\n139: - **AND** each step includes timeout and retry behavior notes\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Code execution flow documented\n142: - **GIVEN** the data flow documentation\n143: - **WHEN** the code execution flow page is viewed\n144: - **THEN** the document shows the execution flow:\n145:   1. Client sends code via Router to sandbox pod\n146:   2. Router validates JWT and routes to correct sandbox\n147:   3. PicoD receives request in sandbox pod\n148:   4. PicoD executes code with workspace isolation\n149:   5. Response returns through Router to client\n150: - **AND** includes error handling scenarios:\n151:   - Timeout during execution\n152:   - Sandbox pod not ready\n153:   - Invalid authentication token\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Session routing flow documented\n156: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n157: - **WHEN** the session routing flow section is viewed\n158: - **THEN** the document explains how Router maintains session state:\n159:   - Redis/Valkey stores session-to-sandbox mappings\n160:   - Session key structure documented (`session:<id>`)\n161:   - Session TTL and cleanup logic\n162: - **AND** includes session lifecycle states:\n163:   - Created, Active, Expired, Terminated\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## REQ-004: Python SDK API Documentation\n168: \n169: ### Description\n170: \n171: Provide complete API documentation for the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) with code examples and type signatures.\n172: \n173: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Python SDK overview page exists\n176: - **GIVEN** the API documentation directory at `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/`\n177: - **WHEN** a user navigates to the SDK overview (`overview.md`)\n178: - **THEN** the page includes:\n179:   - Installation instructions (`pip install agentcube-sdk`)\n180:   - Quick start code example\n181:   - SDK architecture diagram showing Control Plane vs Data Plane\n182:   - Version compatibility table\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient API documented\n185: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK API documentation\n186: - **WHEN** a user views the CodeInterpreterClient API page (`code-interpreter-client.md`)\n187: - **THEN** the document provides complete API reference:\n188:   - Class initialization parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `jwt_token`)\n189:   - `execute_code(language, code, timeout)` method signature and return type\n190:   - `execute_command(command)` method signature\n191:   - `upload_file(path, content)` method\n192:   - `download_file(path)` method\n193:   - `list_files()` method\n194:   - `create_session()` and `stop_session()` methods\n195: - **AND** each method includes:\n196:   - Type annotations (Python 3.10+)\n197:   - Parameter descriptions\n198:   - Return value documentation\n199:   - Exception types that can be raised\n200:   - Code example snippet\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient API documented\n203: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK API documentation\n204: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntimeClient API page (`agent-runtime-client.md`) is viewed\n205: - **THEN** the document includes:\n206:   - Client initialization parameters\n207:   - `invoke_agent(agent_name, input_data)` method\n208:   - Session management for agent invocations\n209:   - Response format documentation\n210: - **AND** provides examples for:\n211:   - Basic agent invocation\n212:   - Session reuse with multiple invocations\n213:   - Error handling patterns\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Exception hierarchy documented\n216: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK API documentation\n217: - **WHEN** a user views the exceptions page (`exceptions.md`)\n218: - **THEN** the document lists all exception types:\n219:   - `AgentCubeError` (base exception)\n220:   - `CommandExecutionError` (code/command failures)\n221:   - `SessionError` (session lifecycle errors)\n222:   - `DataPlaneError` (PicoD communication errors)\n223:   - `AuthenticationError` (JWT validation failures)\n224: - **AND** each exception includes:\n225:   - Inheritance hierarchy\n226:   - Exception attributes (e.g., `exit_code`, `stderr` for CommandExecutionError)\n227:   - Example code showing how to catch and handle the exception\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Session management patterns documented\n230: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK documentation\n231: - **WHEN** the session management page (`sessions.md`) is viewed\n232: - **THEN** the document explains:\n233:   - Session creation and configuration options\n234:   - Session reuse with context manager pattern\n235:   - Explicit session termination\n236:   - Session timeout behavior\n237: - **AND** provides code examples:\n238:   ```python\n239:   # Context manager pattern\n240:   with CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:\n241:       client.execute_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")\n242:   # Explicit session management\n243:   client = CodeInterpreterClient(...)\n244:   session = client.create_session()\n245:   client.execute_code(\"python\", \"code\", session_id=session.id)\n246:   client.stop_session(session.id)\n247:   ```\n248: \n249: ---\n250: \n251: ## REQ-005: Go Client API Documentation\n252: \n253: ### Description\n254: \n255: Provide complete API documentation for the Go client (`client-go`) with Kubernetes-native patterns and type signatures.\n256: \n257: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Go client overview page exists\n260: - **GIVEN** the API documentation directory at `docs/docs/api/client-go/`\n261: - **WHEN** a user navigates to the Go client overview (`overview.md`)\n262: - **THEN** the page includes:\n263:   - Installation via Go module (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`)\n264:   - Kubernetes client-go integration explanation\n265:   - CRD types (`AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`)\n266:   - Version compatibility with Kubernetes versions\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Clientset construction documented\n269: - **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n270: - **WHEN** a user views the Clientset documentation (`clientset.md`)\n271: - **THEN** the document provides:\n272:   - `NewForConfig(config *rest.Config)` function signature\n273:   - `NewForConfigOrDie(config)` panic variant\n274:   - Clientset interface methods (`RuntimeV1alpha1()`, `Discovery()`)\n275: - **AND** includes code example:\n276:   ```go\n277:   config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfigPath)\n278:   clientset, err := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n279:   runtimeClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n280:   ```\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRUD operations documented\n283: - **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n284: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime operations page (`agent-runtime-crud.md`) is viewed\n285: - **THEN** the document lists all CRUD methods:\n286:   - `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n287:   - `Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})`\n288:   - `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n289:   - `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n290:   - `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n291:   - `Delete(ctx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n292:   - `DeleteCollection(ctx, metav1.DeleteOptions{}, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n293:   - `Patch(ctx, name, patchType, patch, metav1.PatchOptions{})`\n294:   - `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n295: - **AND** each method includes:\n296:   - Go type signatures\n297:   - Parameter descriptions\n298:   - Return types and errors\n299:   - Code example\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRUD operations documented\n302: - **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n303: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter operations page (`code-interpreter-crud.md`) is viewed\n304: - **THEN** the document mirrors AgentRuntime CRUD documentation structure\n305: - **AND** includes examples for all CRUD operations on CodeInterpreter resources\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: Informer and Lister patterns documented\n308: - **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n309: - **WHEN** the informer documentation page (`informer.md`) is viewed\n310: - **THEN** the document explains:\n311:   - `SharedInformerFactory` construction\n312:   - `Start(stopCh)` and `Shutdown()` methods\n313:   - `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` for cache synchronization\n314:   - AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n315:   - Lister interface usage patterns\n316: - **AND** provides code examples:\n317:   ```go\n318:   factory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 30*time.Second)\n319:   informer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\n320:   stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n321:   factory.Start(stopCh)\n322:   factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)\n323:   lister := informer.Lister()\n324:   ar, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n325:   ```\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Fake clientset for testing documented\n328: - **GIVEN** the Go client API documentation\n329: - **WHEN** the testing page (`testing.md`) is viewed\n330: - **THEN** the document explains:\n331:   - `NewSimpleClientset()` for unit testing\n332:   - Adding reactors for custom behavior\n333:   - Object tracking and retrieval\n334:   - Watch simulation in tests\n335: - **AND** includes test example code snippet\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ## REQ-006: CRD Schema Documentation\n340: \n341: ### Description\n342: \n343: Document the Kubernetes Custom Resource Definition schemas for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter.\n344: \n345: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD schema documented\n348: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n349: - **WHEN** a user views the CRD schema page (`crd-agent-runtime.md`)\n350: - **THEN** the document includes:\n351:   - Full YAML schema example\n352:   - Spec fields documentation:\n353:     - `replicas` (integer, default 1)\n354:     - `image` (string, required)\n355:     - `resources` (ResourceRequirements)\n356:     - `env` (array of EnvVar)\n357:     - `volumeMounts` (array)\n358:   - Status fields documentation:\n359:     - `phase` (Running, Pending, Failed)\n360:     - `conditions` (array of Condition)\n361:     - `podName` (string)\n362: - **AND** includes validation rules and default values\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD schema documented\n365: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n366: - **WHEN** a user views the CodeInterpreter CRD schema (`crd-code-interpreter.md`)\n367: - **THEN** the document provides:\n368:   - Full YAML schema example\n369:   - Spec fields:\n370:     - `language` (python, javascript, typescript)\n371:     - `timeout` (duration string)\n372:     - `workspaceSize` (resource quantity)\n373:   - Status fields:\n374:     - `sessionID` (string)\n375:     - `podIP` (string)\n376:     - `lastExecutionTime` (timestamp)\n377: - **AND** includes example YAML manifest\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: CRD API version documented\n380: - **GIVEN** the CRD documentation\n381: - **WHEN** the API version section is viewed\n382: - **THEN** the document states the API group and version:\n383:   - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n384:   - Version: `v1alpha1`\n385: - **AND** explains version stability status and future versioning plans\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: ## REQ-007: Configuration Documentation\n390: \n391: ### Description\n392: \n393: Document configuration options for each binary component with command-line flags and environment variables.\n394: \n395: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Router configuration documented\n398: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n399: - **WHEN** the Router configuration page (`router-config.md`) is viewed\n400: - **THEN** the document lists all configuration options:\n401:   - `--port` (default :8080)\n402:   - `--store-addr` (Redis address)\n403:   - `--store-type` (redis/valkey)\n404:   - `--max-concurrent` (default 1000)\n405:   - `--enable-tls` and `--tls-cert/--tls-key`\n406:   - Environment variable overrides (`PORT`, `STORE_ADDR`, `STORE_TYPE`)\n407: - **AND** each option includes:\n408:   - Default value\n409:   - Valid values/ranges\n410:   - Usage description\n411:   - Example command line\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: WorkloadManager configuration documented\n414: - **GIVEN** the configuration documentation\n415: - **WHEN** the WorkloadManager configuration page (`workloadmanager-config.md`) is viewed\n416: - **THEN** the document lists:\n417:   - `--addr` (HTTP server address)\n418:   - `--gc-interval` (garbage collection interval, default 5m)\n419:   - `--kubeconfig` (Kubernetes config path)\n420:   - HTTP timeout configurations (`--read-timeout`, `--write-timeout`)\n421: - **AND** provides example deployment YAML with configuration\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: PicoD configuration documented\n424: - **GIVEN** the configuration documentation\n425: - **WHEN** the PicoD configuration page (`picod-config.md`) is viewed\n426: - **THEN** the document includes:\n427:   - `--port` (default 8080)\n428:   - `--workspace` (workspace directory path)\n429:   - `--auth-enabled` (JWT authentication toggle)\n430:   - `--max-exec-time` (execution timeout, default 30s)\n431:   - `--max-file-size` (file size limit, default 10MB)\n432:   - `--sanitize-root` (path sanitization root)\n433: - **AND** includes security configuration best practices\n434: \n435: #### Scenario: Agentd configuration documented\n436: - **GIVEN** the configuration documentation\n437: - **WHEN** the Agentd configuration page (`agentd-config.md`) is viewed\n438: - **THEN** the document lists:\n439:   - `--idle-threshold` (default 30m)\n440:   - `--check-interval` (default 5m)\n441:   - `--max-concurrent-cleanup` (default 10)\n442:   - `--leader-election` (default true)\n443:   - `--namespace` (watched namespaces)\n444: - **AND** explains leader election configuration\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ## REQ-008: Deployment Documentation\n449: \n450: ### Description\n451: \n452: Provide deployment guides for installing AgentCube on Kubernetes with Helm charts.\n453: \n454: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: Helm installation guide documented\n457: - **GIVEN** the deployment documentation directory at `docs/docs/deployment/`\n458: - **WHEN** the Helm installation page (`helm-installation.md`) is viewed\n459: - **THEN** the document provides:\n460:   - Helm chart location\n461:   - Installation command: `helm install agentcube ./manifests/helm/agentcube`\n462:   - Required values configuration:\n463:     - Redis/Valkey connection settings\n464:     - JWT configuration\n465:     - Kubernetes namespace\n466:   - Optional values table\n467: - **AND** includes post-installation verification steps\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: Prerequisites documented\n470: - **GIVEN** the deployment documentation\n471: - **WHEN** the prerequisites page (`prerequisites.md`) is viewed\n472: - **THEN** the document lists:\n473:   - Kubernetes version requirements (≥1.24)\n474:   - Required cluster resources (CPU, memory)\n475:   - Redis/Valkey deployment\n476:   - Helm 3 installation\n477:   - kubectl configuration\n478: - **AND** provides setup commands for each prerequisite\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Multi-namespace deployment documented\n481: - **GIVEN** the deployment documentation\n482: - **WHEN** the multi-namespace deployment page (`multi-namespace.md`) is viewed\n483: - **THEN** the document explains:\n484:   - Deploying Router and WorkloadManager in separate namespaces\n485:   - Cross-namespace communication configuration\n486:   - RBAC requirements for multi-namespace access\n487: - **AND** includes YAML examples for namespace-scoped deployment\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: TLS and security configuration documented\n490: - **GIVEN** the deployment documentation\n491: - **WHEN** the security configuration page (`security.md`) is viewed\n492: - **THEN** the document provides:\n493:   - TLS certificate configuration for Router\n494:   - JWT signing key management\n495:   - RBAC configuration for WorkloadManager\n496:   - Network policies for pod isolation\n497:   - Secret management best practices\n498: - **AND** includes example YAML configurations for each security setting\n499: \n500: ---\n501: \n502: ## REQ-009: Examples and Tutorials\n503: \n504: ### Description\n505: \n506: Provide example applications and tutorials demonstrating AgentCube usage patterns.\n507: \n508: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: PCAP analyzer example documented\n511: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation\n512: - **WHEN** the examples page (`examples.md`) is viewed\n513: - **THEN** the document includes:\n514:   - PCAP analyzer application description\n515:   - Architecture diagram showing LangChain + AgentCube integration\n516:   - Setup and deployment instructions\n517:   - Code walkthrough for key components\n518: - **AND** provides link to full source code in `example/pcap-analyzer/`\n519: \n520: #### Scenario: Quick start tutorial documented\n521: - **GIVEN** the getting-started documentation\n522: - **WHEN** the quick start tutorial (`first-sandbox.md`) is viewed\n523: - **THEN** the document provides step-by-step guide:\n524:   1. Install AgentCube via Helm\n525:   2. Configure Python SDK connection\n526:   3. Create first sandbox session\n527:   4. Execute Python code\n528:   5. Upload and download files\n529:   6. Clean up session\n530: - **AND** each step includes code examples and expected output\n531: \n532: #### Scenario: LangChain integration tutorial documented\n533: - **GIVEN** the examples documentation\n534: - **WHEN** the LangChain integration page (`langchain-tutorial.md`) is viewed\n535: - **THEN** the document provides:\n536:   - LangChain tool wrapper implementation\n537:   - Agent workflow with code execution\n538:   - Session management in multi-turn conversations\n539:   - Error handling patterns\n540: - **AND** includes runnable code snippets\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## REQ-010: Documentation Navigation and Cross-References\n545: \n546: ### Description\n547: \n548: Ensure documentation has proper navigation structure and cross-references between related topics.\n549: \n550: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: Sidebar navigation configured correctly\n553: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus sidebars configuration at `docs/sidebars.ts`\n554: - **WHEN** the sidebars configuration is viewed\n555: - **THEN** the file includes:\n556:   - `architecture` sidebar with autogenerated directory\n557:   - `api` sidebar with Python SDK and Go Client categories\n558:   - `deployment` sidebar for deployment guides\n559: - **AND** each sidebar category has proper labels and descriptions\n560: \n561: #### Scenario: Architecture to API cross-references exist\n562: - **GIVEN** the architecture documentation pages\n563: - **WHEN** an architecture page discusses a component\n564: - **THEN** the page includes Docusaurus links to relevant API documentation:\n565:   - Router architecture → Go Client router endpoints\n566:   - PicoD architecture → Python SDK code execution API\n567:   - CRD architecture → Go Client CRUD operations\n568: - **AND** links use proper Docusaurus link syntax\n569: \n570: #### Scenario: API to deployment cross-references exist\n571: - **GIVEN** the API documentation pages\n572: - **WHEN** an API page documents client configuration\n573: - **THEN** the page links to deployment configuration documentation\n574: - **AND** includes links to Helm value configuration\n575: \n576: #### Scenario: Documentation index page exists\n577: - **GIVEN** the documentation site\n578: - **WHEN** a user visits the documentation root\n579: - **THEN** an index page (`docs/docs/intro.md`) exists\n580: - **AND** the page provides:\n581:   - Overview of AgentCube\n582:   - Quick links to Getting Started, Architecture, API, Deployment\n583:   - Documentation structure diagram\n584: \n585: ---\n586: \n587: ## REQ-011: Documentation Quality and Completeness\n588: \n589: ### Description\n590: \n591: Ensure documentation meets quality standards for technical accuracy, readability, and completeness.\n592: \n593: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n594: \n595: #### Scenario: All API methods are documented\n596: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK source code at `sdk-python/`\n597: - **WHEN** documentation generation is verified\n598: - **THEN** every public class method in `CodeInterpreterClient` has a documentation entry\n599: - **AND** every public method in `AgentRuntimeClient` has a documentation entry\n600: - **AND** documentation coverage metric is ≥90%\n601: \n602: #### Scenario: Documentation builds without errors\n603: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus documentation site\n604: - **WHEN** `npm run build` is executed in the `docs/` directory\n605: - **THEN** the build succeeds with no errors\n606: - **AND** all pages are generated correctly\n607: - **AND** no broken internal links are reported\n608: \n609: #### Scenario: Code examples are runnable\n610: - **GIVEN** the documentation code examples\n611: - **WHEN** code examples are tested against a running AgentCube instance\n612: - **THEN** at least 80% of code examples execute successfully\n613: - **AND** examples use realistic parameters and values\n614: - **AND** examples include necessary import statements\n615: \n616: #### Scenario: Documentation is version-controlled\n617: - **GIVEN** the documentation files\n618: - **WHEN** git history is examined\n619: - **THEN** all documentation files are tracked in version control\n620: - **AND** documentation changes are reviewed via pull request process\n621: - **AND** significant documentation updates are mentioned in changelog\n622: \n623: #### Scenario: Documentation has consistent formatting\n624: - **GIVEN** all documentation markdown files\n625: - **WHEN** formatting is validated\n626: - **THEN** all files use consistent markdown style:\n627:   - Headers use ATX style (# syntax)\n628:   - Code blocks have language annotations\n629:   - Tables use GitHub-flavored markdown syntax\n630:   - Lists use consistent indentation (2 spaces)\n631: - **AND** Docusaurus frontmatter (`id`, `title`, `description`) is present where required\n632: \n633: ---\n634: \n635: ## REQ-012: Internationalization Support\n636: \n637: ### Description\n638: \n639: Provide documentation in multiple languages (English as primary, with structure for translations).\n640: \n641: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n642: \n643: #### Scenario: English documentation is primary\n644: - **GIVEN** the documentation directory\n645: - **WHEN** the default documentation locale is examined\n646: - **THEN** all documentation files are written in English\n647: - **AND** English is configured as default locale in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n648: \n649: #### Scenario: Translation structure exists\n650: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus i18n configuration at `docs/i18n/`\n651: - **WHEN** the i18n directory structure is examined\n652: - **THEN** the directory structure supports translations:\n653:   - `i18n/zh-CN/` for Chinese translation\n654:   - `i18n/ja/` for Japanese translation\n655: - **AND** translation JSON files for UI strings exist\n656: \n657: #### Scenario: Locale configuration is correct\n658: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus config\n659: - **WHEN** `i18n` configuration is examined\n660: - **THEN** `docusaurus.config.ts` includes:\n661:   - `defaultLocale: 'en'`\n662:   - `locales: ['en', 'zh-CN', 'ja']`\n663:   - Locale names and labels configured\n664: - **AND** locale switcher UI is enabled\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## REQ-013: Documentation Search and Indexing\n669: \n670: ### Description\n671: \n672: Enable documentation search functionality for users to find relevant content quickly.\n673: \n674: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n675: \n676: #### Scenario: Documentation search is enabled\n677: - **GIVEN** the Docusaurus configuration\n678: - **WHEN** search configuration is examined\n679: - **THEN** a search plugin is configured (e.g., Algolia or local search)\n680: - **AND** search input is visible in documentation navbar\n681: \n682: #### Scenario: Search indexes all documentation pages\n683: - **GIVEN** the search configuration\n684: - **WHEN** search functionality is tested\n685: - **THEN** search results include:\n686:   - Architecture documentation pages\n687:   - API documentation pages\n688:   - Deployment guides\n689:   - Getting started pages\n690: - **AND** search results show page titles and relevant excerpts\n691: \n692: #### Scenario: API methods are searchable\n693: - **GIVEN** the documentation search\n694: - **WHEN** a user searches for \"execute_code\"\n695: - **THEN** the search returns results pointing to:\n696:   - Python SDK code execution documentation\n697:   - Code execution flow architecture\n698:   - Quick start tutorial with execute_code example\n699: - **AND** search results are ranked by relevance\n700: \n701: ---\n702: \n703: ## Summary\n704: \n705: | REQ ID | Component | Deliverables |\n706: |--------|-----------|--------------|\n707: | REQ-001 | Architecture Overview | `overview.md` with system diagram and tech stack |\n708: | REQ-002 | Component Architecture | `router.md`, `workloadmanager.md`, `picod.md`, `agentd.md` |\n709: | REQ-003 | Data Flow | Sandbox creation, code execution, session routing flows |\n710: | REQ-004 | Python SDK API | `overview.md`, `code-interpreter-client.md`, `agent-runtime-client.md`, `exceptions.md`, `sessions.md` |\n711: | REQ-005 | Go Client API | `overview.md`, `clientset.md`, CRUD docs, `informer.md`, `testing.md` |\n712: | REQ-006 | CRD Schema | `crd-agent-runtime.md`, `crd-code-interpreter.md` |\n713: | REQ-007 | Configuration | Config docs for Router, WorkloadManager, PicoD, Agentd |\n714: | REQ-008 | Deployment | Helm guide, prerequisites, multi-namespace, security |\n715: | REQ-009 | Examples | PCAP analyzer, quick start, LangChain tutorial |\n716: | REQ-010 | Navigation | Sidebar config, cross-references, index page |\n717: | REQ-011 | Quality | API coverage, build success, runnable examples |\n718: | REQ-012 | Internationalization | English primary, translation structure |\n719: | REQ-013 | Search | Search plugin configuration and indexing |\n720: \n721: **Total Requirements:** 13  \n722: **Total Scenarios:** 48\n723: \n724: ---\n725: \n726: ## Documentation File Structure\n727: \n728: ```\n729: docs/docs/\n730: ├── architecture/\n731: │   ├── overview.md                 (REQ-001)\n732: │   ├── router.md                   (REQ-002)\n733: │   ├── workloadmanager.md          (REQ-002)\n734: │   ├── picod.md                    (REQ-002)\n735: │   ├── agentd.md                   (REQ-002)\n736: │   ├── data-flow/\n737: │   │   ├── sandbox-creation.md     (REQ-003)\n738: │   │   ├── code-execution.md       (REQ-003)\n739: │   │   └── session-routing.md      (REQ-003)\n740: │   └── crd/\n741: │       ├── agent-runtime.md        (REQ-006)\n742: │       └── code-interpreter.md     (REQ-006)\n743: │\n744: ├── api/\n745: │   ├── sdk-python/\n746: │   │   ├── overview.md             (REQ-004)\n747: │   │   ├── code-interpreter-client.md (REQ-004)\n748: │   │   ├── agent-runtime-client.md    (REQ-004)\n749: │   │   ├── exceptions.md           (REQ-004)\n750: │   │   └── sessions.md             (REQ-004)\n751: │   └── client-go/\n752: │       ├── overview.md             (REQ-005)\n753: │       ├── clientset.md            (REQ-005)\n754: │       ├── agent-runtime-crud.md   (REQ-005)\n755: │       ├── code-interpreter-crud.md (REQ-005)\n756: │       ├── informer.md             (REQ-005)\n757: │       └── testing.md              (REQ-005)\n758: │\n759: ├── deployment/\n76